The paper discusses a framework for reconfigurable state machine replication, which is a topic related to distributed computing and systems. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with state machines, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework on a distributed testbed, which is related to cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also discusses the performance analysis of the framework, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
